rephrase the text using other words "It is worth mentioning that there are groups of nouns that differ from other nouns in terms of number: these nouns have only one form of number. Those nouns that are not singular are called pluralia tantum and those nouns that are exclusively singular are called singularia tantum .
Among the singularia tantum verbal nouns are thinking, messing;
Among the pluralia tantum verbal nouns are savings, belongings.
